diff:1290549973:1290456009:=6,29c6,8%0a%3c I am glad to release simuPOP 1.0.5, which is a maintenance release of%0a%3c the 1.0.x series. Because this release fixes two crash bugs, all users%0a%3c are recommended to upgrade.%0a%3c %0a%3c The most useful feature of this release is the support of parameter%0a%3c subPops in during mating operators. This feature can be used to apply%0a%3c different during-mating operators to offspring according to their%0a%3c properties. For example, sex-specific selection can be implemented by%0a%3c applying different selection operators to virtual subpopulations%0a%3c defined by individual sex; and applying an operator to a virtual%0a%3c subpopulation with affected individuals will effectively discard all%0a%3c unaffected individuals. An operator DiscardIf has been provided to%0a%3c filter offspring according to subpopulations, an expression, or a%0a%3c user-defined function. Please refer to simuPOP ChangeLog for a%0a%3c complete list of bug fixes and new features.%0a%3c %0a%3c With the stabilization of the simuPOP interface, I will pay more%0a%3c attention to the performance of simuPOP. Because many parts of simuPOP%0a%3c can be parallelized, I plan to use openMP and other techniques to%0a%3c improve the efficiency of simuPOP. If your script has been running%0a%3c slowly due to the use of some particular operators, please feel free%0a%3c to let me know.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> I am glad to release simuPOP 1.0.5, which is a maintenance release of the 1.0.x series. In addition to bug fixes, this release adds a number of small features to improve the usability of simuPOP. Please refer to ChangeLog for a list of new features.%0a> %0a> %0a
