diff:1260465117:1260464489:=7,15c7,15%0a%3c After major revisions to the @@pedigree@@ class and the @@simuPOP.sampling@@ module, I am happy to announce the release of simuPOP 0.9.9. This release marks the completion of all new features and the 0.9.x release series. Because simuPOP 1.0 is right around the corner (I plan to release it within a month) and there are likely some interface adjustments, users are not recommended to upgrade to this release unless you are eager to test out the new sampling module.%0a%3c %0a%3c The traditional index-based pedigrees have been replaced by a new ID based pedigree system. Because IDs are invariant across populations, the new system is much easier to work with. The resulting @@simuPOP.sampling@@ module is shorter, but more powerful than the previous one. New features include a combined sampler that allows you to draw different types of samples from a population, and a new @@subPops@@ parameter that allows you to drawn samples from selected virtual subpopulations, such as drawing cases and controls from certain age or ethnic groups. The population and pedigree classes have been modified to reflect this change, with improved @@population.removeSubPops@@, @@population.removeIndividuals@@, @@pedigree.locateRelatives@@, and new member functions @@population.removeInfoFields@@, @@population.extractSubPops@@, @@population.extractIndividuals@@ and @@pedigree.individualsWithRelatives@@. Please refer to the simuPOP user's guide and reference manual for more details about these new features.%0a%3c %0a%3c There are two noticeable changes to the simuPOP user interface. First, parameters and population variables @@numOfMale@@ and @@numOfFemale@@ used in the @@stat@@ operator and some other places have been renamed to @@numOfMales@@ and @@numOfFemales@@ as suggested by a colleague. Second, all global constant variables such as @@ChromosomeX@@ and @@BinomialDistribution@@ have been changed to a @@CAPITAL_LETTER_WITH_UNDERSCORE@@ style. The previous style tends to be confusing because it is also used for global functions.%0a%3c %0a%3c In addition, a new module simuPOP.gsl is added to simuPOP that exposes some GSL (GNU Scientific Libraries) CDF functions to the user interface. This module is provided for convenience and is in no means a complete wrapper of GSL. Because it is slow and error prone to import submodules such as @@simuPOP.plotter@@ because of their reliance on a third-party module rpy, submodules are no longer loaded by default with @@'from simuPOP import *'@@.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> After major revisions to the pedigree class and the simuPOP.sampling module, I am happy to announce the release of simuPOP 0.9.9. This release marks the end of all new features and the 0.9.x release series. Because simuPOP 1.0 is right around the corner (I plan to release it within a month) and there are likely some interface adjustments, users are not recommended to upgrade to this release unless you are eager to test out the new sampling module.%0a> %0a> The traditional index-based pedigrees have been replaced by a new ID based pedigree system. Because IDs are invariant across populations, the new system is much easier to work with. The resulting simuPOP.sampling module is shorter, but more powerful than the previous one. New features include a combined sampler that allows you to draw different types of samples from a population, and a new subPops parameter that allows you to drawn samples from selected virtual subpopulations, such as drawing cases and controls from certain age or ethnic groups. The population and pedigree classes have been modified to reflect this change, with new member functions population.extractSubPops, population.extractIndividuals and pedigree.individualsWithRelatives. Please refer to the simuPOP user's guide and reference manual for more details about these new features.%0a> %0a> There are two noticeable change to the simuPOP user interface. First, parameters and population variables numOfMale and numOfFemale in the stat operator and some other places have been renamed to numOfMales and numOfFemales as suggested by a colleague. Second, all global constant variables such as ChromosomeX and BinomialDistribution have been changed to a CAPITAL_LETTER_WITH_UNDERSCORE style. The latter is a well-accepted style for constants in Python and I had to overcome by dislike of all capital letters to make this change.%0a> %0a> A new module simuPOP.gsl is added to simuPOP that exposes some GSL (GNU Scientific Libraries) CDF functions to the user interface. This module is provided for convenience and is in no means a complete wrapper of GSL. In addition, because module simuPOP.plotter relies on a third-party module rpy, it is no longer loaded by default with 'from simuPOP import *'.%0a> %0a> %0a
