diff:1249674017:1249665204:=6,60c6,22%0a%3c The stat operator is the biggest and most complicated operator of%0a%3c simuPOP. There were some long-standing usage problems with this%0a%3c operator but the solutions were far from trivial. Only until last%0a%3c month did I gather some time and energy to rewrite this operator, and%0a%3c I am happy that I did it because with the revision of this operator, I%0a%3c finally see some light of the 1.0 release.%0a%3c %0a%3c The first problem is with variable alleleFreq[loc][allele] and other%0a%3c counting and frequency variables. Because it is difficult to know in%0a%3c advance which alleles are in the population, alleleFreq[loc][allele]%0a%3c might fail. Although I have forced alleleFreq[loc] to have at least%0a%3c two elements, which solves the problem for diallelic markers,%0a%3c alleleFreq[loc][allele] can be invalid in other modules. To address%0a%3c this problem, I have added a special dictionary type defdict to%0a%3c simuPOP, which is now used for allele, genotype, haplotype and%0a%3c heterozygote counts are frequencies. This dictionary returns 0 for%0a%3c unrecognized keys so alleleFreq[loc][allele] will return 0 if%0a%3c specified allele does not exist in a population. Because only existing%0a%3c alleles are listed, alleleFreq[loc].keys() lists available alleles and%0a%3c you can use len(alleleFreq[loc]) to get number of alleles at locus%0a%3c loc. For this reason, statistic numOfAlleles have been removed.%0a%3c %0a%3c The second problem is how to control which variables to output and%0a%3c whether or not to calculate statistics for all subpopulations.%0a%3c Parameters blah_param have been used for each statistic but these%0a%3c parameters were difficult to use. The new stat operator now has a vars%0a%3c parameter that allows you to specify which variables to output, and%0a%3c use special variable names (e.g. alleleFreq_sp) to control whether or%0a%3c not statistics should be calculated for all subpopulations. An%0a%3c additional parameter suffix has been introduced to allow for change of%0a%3c variable names.%0a%3c %0a%3c The new stat operator now supports parameter subPops so that you can%0a%3c calculate statistics for specified (virtual) subpopulations. This%0a%3c makes it easy to calculate partial statistics such as pairwise Fst.%0a%3c More importantly, the use of virtual subpopulations allows you to%0a%3c calculate, for example, allele frequency among cases and controls, and%0a%3c association tests among only smokers.%0a%3c %0a%3c Other than these, there has been several new statistics such as%0a%3c sumOfInfo, meanOfInfo, varOfInfo, minOfInfo, maxOfInfo for the%0a%3c calculation of basic statistics of specified information fields, new%0a%3c genotype based genetic association tests (Chi-square and Armitage%0a%3c trend test), and new statistics for population structure (Nei's Gst).%0a%3c Perhaps more importantly, all statistics of the stat operator has now%0a%3c been carefully documented with examples. Please check the relevant sections of the [[http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/4_userGuide.html#statistics-calculation-operator-stat | user's guide]] and [[http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/3_refManual.html#stat | reference manual]] for details.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c There have been other interface changes. If your scripts use functions%0a%3c rng(), population.ancestor(), nested lists for parameters lociPos and%0a%3c lociNames of function population, and parameter rep of operators,%0a%3c please check the ChangeLog or updated user's guide because these%0a%3c functions and parameters have been changed.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> %0a> If your scripts use functions @@rng()@@, @@population.ancestor()@@, nested lists for parameters @@lociPos@@ and @@lociNames@@ of function population, and parameter @@rep@@ of operators, please check the ChangeLog or updated user's guide because these functions and parameters have been changed.%0a> %0a> Then, your @@stat@@ operator probably will not work because this operator has been rewritten with many changes and new features:%0a> %0a> * Statistic @@numOfAlleles@@ is removed.%0a> * New statistic @@sumOfInfo@@, @@meanOfInfo@@, @@varOfInfo@@, @@minOfInfo@@, @@maxOfInfo@@ for the calculation of basic statistics of specified information fields.%0a> * New genotype based gentic association tests (Chi-square and Armitage trend test).%0a> * New statistics for population structure (Nei's Gst). Rename parameter @@Fst@@ to @@structure@@.%0a> * A parameter @@vars@@ is now used to control which variables to output. Statistics in subpopulations are now not calculated by default. All previous @@_param@@ parameters have been removed.%0a> * A parameter @@suffix@@ is added to allow you add a suffix to the names of outputted variables.%0a> * This operator now supports parameter @@subPops@@ so that you can calculate statistics for specified (virtual) subpopulations.%0a> * Tuples are now used as dictionary keys for genotype and haplotypes.%0a> * A special dictionary type has been introduced for allele, genotype, haplotype and heterozygote counts are frequencies. This dictionary returns 0 for unrecognized keys so @@alleleFreq[loc][allele]@@ will return 0 if specified allele does not exist in a population. Because only existing alleles are listed, @@alleleFreq[loc].keys()@@ lists available alleles and you can use @@len(alleleFreq[loc])@@ to get number of alleles at locus @@loc@@.%0a> %0a> Perhaps most importantly, all statistics of the @@stat@@ operator has now been carefully documented with examples. Please check the relevant sections of the [[http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/4_userGuide.html#statistics-calculation-operator-stat | user's guide]] and [[http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/3_refManual.html#stat | reference manual]] for details.%0a> %0a
