diff:1249665053:1249621287:=7,22c7%0a%3c If your scripts use functions @@rng()@@, @@population.ancestor()@@, nested lists for parameters @@lociPos@@ and @@lociNames@@ of function population, and parameter @@rep@@ of operators, please check the ChangeLog or updated user's guide because these functions and parameters have been changed.%0a%3c %0a%3c Then, your @@stat@@ operator probably will not work because this operator has been rewritten with many changes and new features:%0a%3c %0a%3c * Statistic @@numOfAlleles@@ is removed.%0a%3c * New statistic @@sumOfInfo@@, @@meanOfInfo@@, @@varOfInfo@@, @@minOfInfo@@, @@maxOfInfo@@ for the calculation of basic statistics of specified information fields.%0a%3c * New genotype based gentic association tests (Chi-square and Armitage trend test).%0a%3c * New statistics for population structure (Nei's Gst). Rename parameter @@Fst@@ to @@structure@@.%0a%3c * A parameter @@vars@@ is now used to control which variables to output. Statistics in subpopulations are now not calculated by default.%0a%3c * A parameter @@suffix@@ is added to allow you add a suffix to the names of outputted variables.%0a%3c * This operator now supports parameter @@subPops@@ so that you can calculate statistics for specified (virtual) subpopulations.%0a%3c * Tuples are now used as dictionary keys for genotype and haplotypes.%0a%3c * A special dictionary type has been introduced for allele, genotype, haplotype and heterozygote counts are frequencies. This dictionary returns 0 for recognized keys so @@alleleFreq[loc][allele]@@ will return 0 if specified allele does not exist in a population. Because only existing alleles are listed, @@alleleFreq[loc].keys()@@ lists available alleles and you can use @@len(alleleFreq[loc])@@ to get number of alleles at locus @@loc@@.%0a%3c %0a%3c Perhaps most importantly, all statistics of the @@stat@@ operator has now been carefully documented with examples. Please check the relevant sections of the [[http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/4_userGuide.html#statistics-calculation-operator-stat | user's guide]] and [[http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/3_refManual.html#stat | reference manual]] for details.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> %0a
