diff:1245706641:1245688004:=7,33c7,10%0a%3c %0a%3c I am glad to announce the release of simuPOP 0.9.5. This release is%0a%3c marked by significant improvements in mutation operators. Many new%0a%3c mutators have been added with new features introduced to existing%0a%3c mutators. For example:%0a%3c # Mutators can now be applied to virtual subpopulations (e.g. sex different mutation rates)%0a%3c # A new matrixMutator that mutates alleles according to a mutation rate matrix.%0a%3c # Specialized mutators for diallelic and nucleotide loci (snpMutator and acgtMutator).%0a%3c # New mixedMutator that can apply multiple mutators with certain probabilities.%0a%3c # New contextMutator that can apply different mutators according to the context of mutated allele.%0a%3c # A new map in and map out feature that allows the use of mutation models when interpretation of alleles differs.%0a%3c %0a%3c The interface of several existing mutators have also been changed. For%0a%3c example, the maxAllele parameter of a kamMutator is changed to k (with%0a%3c a different meaning), and the generalized stepwise mutation model has%0a%3c been merged to smmMutator. Please refer to the updated simuPOP user's%0a%3c guide (http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/4_userGuide.html#mutation)%0a%3c for details.%0a%3c %0a%3c There has been a few other style changes. For example, the preOps and%0a%3c ops parameters of simulator::evolve now accept single-form inputs%0a%3c (ignore [] when there is only one operator). In addition, parameter%0a%3c rate of the recombinator has been renamed to rates because this%0a%3c parameter accepts multiple recombination rates. This change is%0a%3c expected to break a lot of scripts. Please change your scripts%0a%3c accordingly.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> I am glad to announce the release of simuPOP 0.9.5. This release is marked by significant improvements in mutators. Many new mutators have been added (e.g. matrixMutator, snpMutator, acgtMutator, contextMutator and mixedMutator) with new features introduced to existing mutators (applicability to virtual subpopulations, map in and map out of alleles, context-sensitive mutators). Please refer to the updated simuPOP user's guide (http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/4_userGuide.html#mutation) for details.%0a> %0a> There has been a few other style changes. For example, the preOps and ops parameters of simulator::evolve now accept single-form inputs (ignore [] when there is only one operator). In addition, parameter rate of the recombinator has been renamed to rates because this parameter accepts multiple recombination rates. Please change your scripts accordingly.%0a> %0a
