diff:1245688004:1245687722:=7,10c7,10%0a%3c I am glad to announce the release of simuPOP 0.9.5. This release is marked by significant improvements in mutators. Many new mutators have been added (e.g. matrixMutator, snpMutator, acgtMutator, contextMutator and mixedMutator) with new features introduced to existing mutators (applicability to virtual subpopulations, map in and map out of alleles, context-sensitive mutators). Please refer to the updated simuPOP user's guide (http://simupop.sourceforge.net/manual/build/4_userGuide.html#mutation) for details.%0a%3c %0a%3c There has been a few other style changes. For example, the preOps and ops parameters of simulator::evolve now accept single-form inputs (ignore [] when there is only one operator). In addition, parameter rate of the recombinator has been renamed to rates because this parameter accepts multiple recombination rates. Please change your scripts accordingly.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> I am glad to announce the release of simuPOP 0.9.5. This release is %0a> %0a> There has been a few other style changes. For example, the preOps and ops parameters of simulator::evolve now accept single-form inputs (ignore [] when there is only one operator). In addition, parameter rate of a recombinator has been renamed to rates because this parameter accepts multiple recombination rates. Please change your scripts accordingly.%0a> %0a
